			<ns0:name>eaelt...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/103360015124260446450/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">For multi-threaded target, GDB sends 'vCont;s:&amp;lt;tid&amp;gt;' to stub. That means all other threads should remain stopped (in all-stop mode, as default action is not specified).

For single-threaded target, GDB sends 's' command to stub.

At the moment built-in stub does not support 'vCont', so GDB sends 's' even for multi-threaded targets. In response to 's', the stub resumes all threads.
